com.camerontec.util.datamodel.message

Class MessageImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.message.MessageImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PoolableSharedObject, FieldGroup, IndexedBytesFieldImporter, Message, Nullable, OrderedCollection<Field>, OrderedCollectionOfFields, OrderedCollectionOfIntKeyed<Field>, Recyclable

    public class MessageImpl
extends Object
implements Message
    Concrete Message implementation.

    This class may be used as either a standalone message implementation, or as the base class for other message types.

    Although not required, instances of this class are typically created via a MessageFactory obtained from a MessageFactoryBuilder.

      • copy

        public MessageImpl copy()
        Description copied from interface: Message
        Copy this message.

        This operation returns a deep copy of this message. That is, all contained fields and their groups (and so on) are also copied and the resultant structure is identical to this message.

        The copied message inherits this message's managed context. That is, if this is a managed message (e.g. if it was sourced from a pool) then so is the copy. If this is an un-managed message then so is the copy.

        Specified by:
        copy in interface Message
        Returns:
        The deeply copied field.
